ReportText: EXAM: XR CHEST 2 VW HISTORY: fever, cough, wheezing. TECHNIQUE: Frontal and lateral views. COMPARISON: None. FINDINGS: Bilateral central peribronchial cuffing and perihilar infiltrate. No peripheral infiltrate or consolidation. Normal cardiomediastinal silhouette. No pleural fluid or air. No bony abnormality. IMPRESSION: Findings are seen most frequently with viral lower respiratory tract infection and/or asthma. Electronically Signed by: [[PERSONALNAME]] MD on 11/09/2018 7:50 PM
